\b Course Description:\b0\par
This course introduces popular technologies used in creating web applications. Advanced web applications make use of data and services from a variety of online sources and are able to provide users with functions and features through familiar modern HTML interfaces. The course is roughly divided into 3 parts. \par
\par
\b Part 1\b0  - We will briefly focus on some of the new front end web development standards related to creating web pages. Familiarity with some new tools and concepts such as CSS preprocessors and other shorthand markup languages. After a brief exploration of front end technologies, you will learn about the popular Bootstrap framework often used for responsive designs. Use of source version control via Git will be covered in detail. Having a proper source version control workflow can be extremely helpful in work with groups. PHP/MySQL will also be introduced during this part of the course. Students will be introduced to using a PHP development environment with debugging capabilities. \par
\b Part 2\b0  - The second part of the course will include further application of PHP and the usage of PHP frameworks. We will spend a considerable amount of time with PHP and CodeIgniter framework. Also covered will be use of jQuery, AJAX and possibly other current JavaScript oriented technologies.  Fundamentals of XML and JSON data structure formats will be explored. \par
\b Part 3\b0  \endash  During the third part of the course we will cover the use of web services and APIs and creating web services to be used by web applications or mobile applications. Finally, mobile development will be explored using the flexible and web developer oriented Cordova/PhoneGap technology. Angular/ionic may be introduced in this section as time allows.\par
\par
\b Throughout the class, our emphasis will be on responsive mobile-first compatible designs and choosing elegant, clean, structured framework-leveraged solutions over convoluted ones.\par
